From: Yanghan Ye <yyh94306@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 00:18:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7996: use txrate STBC bit when decoding TXS
 rate

The mt7996 TXS decode path derives the exported station TX bitrate from
MT_TXS0_TX_RATE, but unlike the generic connac helper it reads the STBC
flag from MT_TXS3_RATE_STBC instead of MT_TX_RATE_STBC.

For some EHT stations this results in the reported NSS being halved,
causing userspace to see rates like 2882.3 Mbit/s @ 320 MHz EHT MCS 13
NSS 1 even though the peer is operating at 2 spatial streams.

Align mt7996 with the generic mt76 connac TXS rate decode and use the
STBC bit embedded in the txrate field itself.

Signed-off-by: Yanghan Ye <yyh94306@gmail.com>

diff --git a/mt7996/mac.c b/mt7996/mac.c
index 794d4fe4ba57..68103460d634 100644
--- a/mt7996/mac.c
+++ b/mt7996/mac.c
@@ -1322,7 +1322,7 @@ mt7996_mac_add_txs_skb(struct mt7996_dev *dev, struct mt76_wcid *wcid,
 
 	rate.mcs = FIELD_GET(MT_TX_RATE_IDX, txrate);
 	rate.nss = FIELD_GET(MT_TX_RATE_NSS, txrate) + 1;
-	stbc = le32_get_bits(txs_data[3], MT_TXS3_RATE_STBC);
+	stbc = FIELD_GET(MT_TX_RATE_STBC, txrate);
 
 	if (stbc && rate.nss > 1)
 		rate.nss >>= 1;
